## When to Use IDs vs Classes

### Use IDs for:

1. **Form label associations**
   ```html
   <label for="user-email-input">Email</label>
   <input id="user-email-input" type="email">
   ```

2. **JavaScript/Stimulus targeting**
   ```javascript
   document.getElementById('user-menu-toggle-button')
   ```

3. **Page anchors for deep linking**
   ```html
   <h2 id="comments-section">Comments</h2>
   <a href="#comments-section">Jump to comments</a>
   ```

4. **Unique page elements**
   - Main navigation
   - Hero section
   - Footer

5. **ARIA relationships**
   ```html
   <button aria-describedby="help-tooltip">Help</button>
   <div id="help-tooltip" role="tooltip">...</div>
   ```

### Use Classes for:

1. **Styling (TailwindCSS utilities)**
   ```html
   <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
   ```

2. **Multiple elements with same style**
   ```html
   <button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
   <button class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
   ```

3. **Component variants**
   ```html
   <div class="card card--featured">
   ```

4. **Responsive design**
   ```html
   <div class="hidden md:block">
   ```

5. **State changes**
   ```html
   <div class="is-active is-loading">
   ```

